From f403639c3916133f5b89f17345940ee32965648d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 19:56:15 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 116/174] =?UTF-8?q?mm,=20arm64:=20vmap=5Fpte=5Frange=20hug?=
 =?UTF-8?q?e-pte=20uses=20paddr=20=E2=80=94=20fixes=20PGCL>0=20SMP=20IPI?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

aarch64 PGCL=6 SMP=2 hung at "smp: Bringing up secondary CPUs ..." after
CPU1 booted but never received IPIs from CPU0.  Root cause: ioremap of
GIC CPU interface (phys 0x8010000, size 64KB) was mapped to wrong
physical pages.

In `vmap_pte_range`, when the CONT_PTE huge-mapping branch fires, the
PTE entry was built via `pfn_pte(paddr >> PAGE_SHIFT, prot)`.  On
PGCL>0 with PAGE_SIZE > MMUPAGE_SIZE, this discards sub-PAGE bits of
paddr.  At PGCL=6 (PAGE_SIZE=256KB) the GICC paddr 0x8010000
truncates to pfn 0x20 → physical 0x8000000 (the GICD), so all 16
CONT-marked PTEs for the GICC region pointed at GICD instead.  CPU1's
gic_cpu_init writes to GICC_CTRL went to GICD; CPU1's CPU interface
was never enabled and SGIs (IPI_RESCHEDULE etc.) were dropped.

Build the huge-pte entry directly from paddr via `__phys_to_pte_val`,
matching the fallthrough non-huge path.

Also fix `arch/arm64/mm/hugetlbpage.c` num_contig_ptes/find_num_contig
which used `*pgsize = PAGE_SIZE` for the CONT_PTE_SIZE case.  At PGCL>0
the per-PTE stride must be MMUPAGE_SIZE (the hardware page size) so
__set_ptes_anysz advances PFN by 1 per CONT-PTE entry; with
PAGE_SIZE/MMUPAGE_SIZE=64 stride the 16 CONT entries would span 4MB
of physical instead of 64KB.

Verified: aarch64 PGCL=6 SMP=2 boots cleanly to LTP (was hung at
"Bringing up secondary CPUs ..." for 60s+).  SMP=1 still works.
SMP=4 hits a separate vmalloc bug (init_IRQ → vmap_small_pages_range
NULL page) not addressed here.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/arm64/mm/hugetlbpage.c |  4 ++--
 mm/vmalloc.c                | 12 +++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 13 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/mm/hugetlbpage.c b/arch/arm64/mm/hugetlbpage.c
index 859c85d471e0..5197c1a50ba4 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/mm/hugetlbpage.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/mm/hugetlbpage.c
@@ -83,7 +83,7 @@ static int find_num_contig(struct mm_struct *mm, unsigned long addr,
 	pud_t *pudp;
 	pmd_t *pmdp;
 
-	*pgsize = PAGE_SIZE;
+	*pgsize = MMUPAGE_SIZE;
 	p4dp = p4d_offset(pgdp, addr);
 	pudp = pud_offset(p4dp, addr);
 	pmdp = pmd_offset(pudp, addr);
@@ -106,7 +106,7 @@ static inline int num_contig_ptes(unsigned long size, size_t *pgsize)
 		contig_ptes = CONT_PMDS;
 		break;
 	case CONT_PTE_SIZE:
-		*pgsize = PAGE_SIZE;
+		*pgsize = MMUPAGE_SIZE;
 		contig_ptes = CONT_PTES;
 		break;
 	default:
diff --git a/mm/vmalloc.c b/mm/vmalloc.c
index 85824af63950..37278cafc8c0 100644
--- a/mm/vmalloc.c
+++ b/mm/vmalloc.c
@@ -124,7 +124,17 @@ static int vmap_pte_range(pmd_t *pmd, unsigned long addr, unsigned long end,
 			size = arch_vmap_pte_range_map_size(addr, end, pfn,
 							    max_page_shift);
 			if (size != PAGE_SIZE && size != MMUPAGE_SIZE) {
-				pte_t entry = pfn_pte(pfn, prot);
+				/*
+				 * pfn_pte(pfn, prot) at PGCL>0 with
+				 * paddr >> PAGE_SHIFT discards sub-PAGE
+				 * bits.  For MMIO ioremap whose paddr
+				 * may be MMUPAGE-aligned but not
+				 * PAGE-aligned (e.g. GICC at 0x8010000
+				 * under PAGE_SIZE=256KB), construct the
+				 * PTE directly from paddr.
+				 */
+				pte_t entry = __pte(__phys_to_pte_val(paddr) |
+						    pgprot_val(prot));
 
 				entry = arch_make_huge_pte(entry, ilog2(size),
 							   0);
